node.title: Queensland records another community case of COVID-19 in border town of Goondiwindi
node.description: Queensland authorities record a case of COVID-19 in the southern border town of Goondiwindi.
node.content:
["Queensland has recorded one new case\u00a0of COVID-19 in the past 24 hours, in the southern border town of Goondiwindi, Health Minister Yvette D'Ath says.", "Ms D'Ath said the woman in her 20s is from Goondwindi and is in home quarantine but could have spent one day in the community.", "Four\u00a0people in the town \u2014 all of them women \u2014 have tested positive to COVID this week.\u00a0", "On Friday, officials said three of those cases were linked to a known cluster in Moree, in northern New South Wales, with Queensland's Acting Chief Health Officer Peter Aitken saying they may have been linked to a NSW woman who was in Goondiwindi for one day to do \"essential shopping\".", "Moree has been excluded from Queensland's border bubble.", "Ms D'Ath said the latest woman to test positive would be sent the Gold Coast University Hospital.", "\"This virus is close on our doorstep and could arrive at any time and we need to continue to come out and get tested,\" she said.", "Speaking at one of the 25 Bunnings stores in Queensland hosting pop-up vaccination clinics this weekend, Ms D'Ath said Queensland was \"so very close now\" to hitting the 80 per cent single-dose vaccination mark.", "But she said one in five Queenslanders aged 16 and older are still yet to be vaccinated.", "
Woman flies Cairns to Darwin, tests positive
", "Dr Aitken said he was also concerned about another case involving a young woman who had flown from\u00a0Cairns to Darwin about a week ago.", "He had been in touch with Northern Territory health authorities to determine where the woman had been and how she caught the Delta variant.\u00a0", "\"Interviews are happening today. We should know later this afternoon where she has been,\" he said.\u00a0", "
NT travellers to quarantine
", "Queensland Health has also declared the Katherine region in the NT a COVID-19 hotspot, following advice from the NT government.", "Anyone arriving into Queensland who has been in Katherine since November 4 will need to isolate in home quarantine until they receive a negative COVID-19 result.", "Anyone who enters Queensland from the Katherine region after 6:00pm on Saturday will be directed to isolate in hotel quarantine until the hotspot declaration is lifted or 14 days of hotel quarantine is completed, whichever comes first.", "Late on Friday, Dr Aitken said anyone who has been in a declared COVID exposure site during the risk period needs to get tested immediately.", "\"Anyone who is planning to visit the Northern Territory, in particular Katherine, should reconsider their need to travel,\" he said.", "", "
